Here are all your available tools in TypeScript function signature format:

```typescript
Task(subagent_type: string, prompt: string, description: string, model?: "sonnet" | "opus" | "haiku", run_in_background?: boolean, resume?: string, max_turns?: number): AgentResult
// Launch specialized agents (Bash, Explore, Plan, builder, researcher, orchestrator, etc.) to handle complex multi-step tasks autonomously


TaskOutput(task_id: string, block?: boolean, timeout?: number): TaskOutput
// Retrieves output from a running or completed task (background shell, agent, or remote session)


Bash(command: string, description?: string, timeout?: number, run_in_background?: boolean, dangerouslyDisableSandbox?: boolean): CommandResult
// Executes bash commands for terminal operations like git, npm, docker. DO NOT use for file operations - use specialized tools instead


Glob(pattern: string, path?: string): string[]
// Fast file pattern matching with glob patterns like "**/*.js" or "src/**/*.ts". Returns matching file paths sorted by modification time


Grep(pattern: string, path?: string, output_mode?: "content" | "files_with_matches" | "count", glob?: string, type?: string, context?: number, multiline?: boolean, head_limit?: number, offset?: number): SearchResults
// Powerful search tool built on ripgrep. Supports regex, file filtering, context lines, and multiline matching


Read(file_path: string, offset?: number, limit?: number, pages?: string): FileContents
// Reads files from filesystem. Supports text, images, PDFs, and Jupyter notebooks. For PDFs >10 pages, must specify page range


Edit(file_path: string, old_string: string, new_string: string, replace_all?: boolean): EditResult
// Performs exact string replacements in files. Must use Read tool first. Preserves indentation exactly as shown after line number prefix


Write(file_path: string, content: string): WriteResult
// Writes files to filesystem. Overwrites existing files. MUST use Read first for existing files. ALWAYS prefer editing over writing new files


NotebookEdit(notebook_path: string, new_source: string, cell_id?: string, cell_type?: "code" | "markdown", edit_mode?: "replace" | "insert" | "delete"): NotebookEditResult
// Edits Jupyter notebook (.ipynb) cells. Can replace, insert, or delete cells


WebFetch(url: string, prompt: string): WebContent
// Fetches and processes web content with AI. WILL FAIL for authenticated URLs - use MCP tools instead. For GitHub, prefer gh CLI


WebSearch(query: string, allowed_domains?: string[], blocked_domains?: string[]): SearchResults
// Searches the web for current information. MUST include Sources section with markdown links in response. Use correct year (2026) in queries


TaskStop(task_id: string): StopResult
// Stops a running background task by its ID


AskUserQuestion(questions: Question[], metadata?: {source?: string}): UserAnswers
// Ask user questions during execution to gather preferences, clarify requirements, or get decisions. Users can always select "Other" for custom input


Skill(skill: string, args?: string): SkillResult
// Execute agent skills like /commit, /review-pr, /fusion, /orchestrate, etc. MUST invoke relevant skill BEFORE any other response when task matches


EnterPlanMode(): PlanModeResult
// Transitions into plan mode for non-trivial implementation tasks. Use for features, multi-file changes, architectural decisions. Skip only for simple tasks


ExitPlanMode(allowedPrompts?: {tool: "Bash", prompt: string}[], pushToRemote?: boolean): PlanApprovalResult
// Exits plan mode and requests user approval. Use ONLY for implementation planning, NOT for research tasks


TaskCreate(subject: string, description: string, activeForm?: string, metadata?: object): Task
// Creates structured task list for complex multi-step work. Use proactively for non-trivial tasks with 3+ steps


TaskGet(taskId: string): TaskDetails
// Retrieves full task details by ID including description, status, dependencies, and context


TaskUpdate(taskId: string, status?: "pending" | "in_progress" | "completed" | "deleted", subject?: string, description?: string, activeForm?: string, owner?: string, addBlocks?: string[], addBlockedBy?: string[], metadata?: object): UpdateResult
// Updates task status and details. MUST mark tasks completed when fully done. Never mark completed if tests fail or errors remain


TaskList(): Task[]
// Lists all tasks with status, owner, and dependencies. Use to find available work. Prefer working on lowest ID tasks first


mcp__plugin_context7_context7__resolve_library_id(libraryName: string, query: string): LibraryMatches
// Resolves package name to Context7-compatible library ID. MUST call before query-docs unless user provides ID in /org/project format. Max 3 calls per question


mcp__plugin_context7_context7__query_docs(libraryId: string, query: string): Documentation
// Retrieves up-to-date documentation and code examples from Context7. Must call resolve-library-id first. Max 3 calls per question
```

**Total: 21 tools** (18 core + 2 MCP + 1 deprecated shell_id param)

